'''''Mamay''''' ({{lang-uk|Мамай}}) is a [[2003 in film|2003]] [[Ukrainian language]] [[film]]. Based on ancient Ukrainian and [[Crimean Tatars|Crimean Tatar]] folklore, this is a Ukrainian version of ''[[Romeo and Juliet]]''. A [[Cossack Mamay|fugitive Cossack]] falls in love with a stunningly beautiful Tatar woman who saves him from certain death. Their love defies age-old hatred between their respective peoples. The film features cinematography by [[Serhiy Mykhalchuk]] and a soundtrack by composer [[Alla Zahaykevych]]. It was directed by [[Oles Sanin]]. ''Mamay'' was Ukraine's 2003 submission for an [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film]].
